The Hero’s Journey, also known as the monomyth, is a narrative structure identified by mythologist Joseph Campbell. It describes a hero who embarks on an adventure, faces and overcomes a crisis, and returns transformed. This framework is ubiquitous, appearing in ancient myths, religious texts, and blockbusters like &ldquo;Harry Potter&rdquo; and &ldquo;Star Wars.&rdquo;
The journey typically involves several key stages:
Protagonist: The hero of the story, is often an ordinary person. Shift: A significant change that sets the hero on their path.
